weather_df = 
  rnoaa::meteo_pull_monitors(c("USW00094728", "USC00519397", "USS0023B17S"),
                      var = c("PRCP", "TMIN", "TMAX"), 
                      date_min = "2017-01-01",
                      date_max = "2017-12-31") %>%
  mutate(
    name = recode(id, USW00094728 = "CentralPark_NY", 
                      USC00519397 = "Waikiki_HA",
                      USS0023B17S = "Waterhole_WA"),
    tmin = tmin / 10,
    tmax = tmax / 10,
    month = lubridate::floor_date(date, unit = "month")) %>%
  select(name, id, date, month, everything())

#2x2 tables

#exposure is either Central Park or Waterhold therefore make expsoure not Waikiki , outome is cold or not cold
#case when helps to make new variable
#true "" command gives you a blank spot 
#janitor command allows it to 
weather_df %>% 
    filter(name != "Waikiki_HA") %>% 
  mutate(
    cold = case_when(
      tmax < 5 ~ "cold",
      tmax >=5 ~ "not_cold",
      TRUE     ~ ""
  )) %>% 
 janitor::tabyl(name, cold)
##            name cold not_cold
##  CentralPark_NY   44      321
##    Waterhole_WA  172      193

#na.rm = TRUE takes the NA out of the dataset so a mean or median can be computed correctly

weather_df %>%
  group_by(name) %>%
  summarize(
    n = n(),
    mean_tmax = mean(tmax, na.rm = TRUE),
    sd_tmax = sd(tmax),
    median_prcp = median(prcp, na.rm = TRUE))
## # A tibble: 3 x 5
##   name               n mean_tmax sd_tmax median_prcp
##   <chr>          <int>     <dbl>   <dbl>       <dbl>
## 1 CentralPark_NY   365     17.4     9.86           0
## 2 Waikiki_HA       365     29.7    NA              0
## 3 Waterhole_WA     365      7.48    7.96           0
weather_df %>%
  group_by(name, month) %>%
  summarize(
    n = n(),
    mean_tmax = mean(tmax, na.rm = TRUE),
    sd_tmax = sd(tmax),
    median_prcp = median(prcp, na.rm = TRUE)
    )%>%
  ggplot(aes(x = month, y = mean_tmax, color = name)) +
    geom_point() + geom_line() + 
    theme(legend.position = "bottom")

#creates a nicely formed table using knitr file

weather_df %>%
  group_by(name, month) %>%
  summarize(mean_tmax = mean(tmax)) %>% 
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = name,
    values_from = mean_tmax) %>% 
  knitr::kable(digits = 1)

#mutate within the groups, create new variale that is the mean tmax

weather_df %>%
  group_by(name) %>%
  mutate(
    mean_tmax = mean(tmax, na.rm = TRUE),
    centered_tmax = tmax - mean(tmax)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = date, y = centered_tmax, color = name)) + 
    geom_point() 
## Warning: Removed 365 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

#window functions in grouped mutates #adds new variable for the tmax rank that ranks the tmax values from highest to lowest or lowest to highest

weather_df %>%
  group_by(name, month) %>%
  mutate(
    tmax_rank = min_rank(tmax)
    ) %>%
  filter(tmax_rank == 1)
